Package: gtkdialog3
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: utility for building GTK3 dialogs from shell scripts
 GtkDialog3 is a program that reads an XML-like description of a dialog
 and creates the corresponding GTK3 user interface.  It can be driven
 from shell scripts to build rich graphical interfaces with buttons,
 text entries, lists, trees, notebooks, terminal emulators, web browsers,
 and source code editors.

Package: gtkdialog3-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: gtkdialog3 (= ${source:Version})
Description: documentation and examples for gtkdialog3
 This package contains the Texinfo manual, PDF documentation,
 info pages, and example scripts for gtkdialog3.
